display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>, consider the open subset <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[U_{y}\subseteq  X]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[y\in  U_{y}]]></fr:tex> and there is a disjoint open subset containing <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex>, so <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x\notin  U_{y}]]></fr:tex>. We claim the union of all such <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[U_{y}]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[y\neq  x]]></fr:tex> is <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[U=\bigcup _{y\in  X\setminus \{x\}}U_{y}]]></fr:tex> is an open subset of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[U^{\complement }=\{x\}]]></fr:tex>. Hence <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\{x\}]]></fr:tex> is closed, as desired.</fr:p><html:span
